    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AssetLoader
    Manages all game assets, such as images and animations.
    AttackingState
    Implements the "Attacking" state for an enemy's state machine.
    AudioManager
    Manages all audio playback for the game, including sound effects (SFX) and music.
    Directions
    Represents the four cardinal directions used for movement and orientation of entities.
    Elevator
    Represents the game's elevator, managing its state, movement between floors, and position.
    ElevatorView
    Renders the elevator scene, including the moving shaft background, the static cabin, and the player.
    EmptyTile
    Represents an empty, non-solid tile in the game world.
    Enemy
    An abstract base class for all enemy entities in the game.
    EnemyAnimationSet
    A data container that holds pre-sliced animation frames for a specific type of enemy.
    EnemyBehavior
    Defines the contract for an enemy's behavior strategy.
    EnemyFactory
    A factory class for creating different types of enemies.
    EnemyState
    Enumerates the possible states for an enemy's state machine.
    EnemyStateHandler
    Defines the contract for a specific state in an enemy's state machine.
    EnemyType
    Enumerates the different types of enemies in the game.
    EnemyView
    Renders an enemy entity on the screen.
    Entity
    An abstract base class for all dynamic game objects, such as the player and enemies.
    FurnitureTile
    Represents an interactable piece of furniture in the game world.
    FurnitureType
    Enumerates the different types of furniture that can appear in a level.
    GameConstants
    An abstract class that holds global, static constants for the game.
    GameController
    The main controller of the game.
    GameModel
    The central data model for the entire game.
    GameoverHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the Game Over screen.
    GameoverView
    Renders the "Game Over" screen.
    GameSession
    Represents the state of a single gameplay session.
    GameState
    Enumerates the possible high-level states of the game.
    HUDView
    Renders the Heads-Up Display (HUD) on the screen during active gameplay.
    IdleState
    Implements the "Idle" state for an enemy's state machine.
    InputHandler
    Centralized input manager for handling all keyboard and mouse events.
    JImpossibleMission
    The main entry point for the JImpossibleMission game.
    LeaderboardHandler
    Handles the logic for the leaderboard screen.
    LeaderboardView
    Renders the leaderboard screen.
    Level
    Represents a single game level.
    LevelLoader
    A utility class for loading game levels from text files.
    LevelView
    Renders the game level, including all its tiles (walls, platforms, furniture, etc.).
    LiftTile
    Represents a solid, vertically moving lift (elevator platform) within a level.
    MainGamePanel
    The main container panel for the entire game, extending JPanel.
    MainMenuHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the main menu screen.
    MainMenuView
    Renders the main menu screen of the game.
    MovingRobot
    Represents a mobile enemy robot that patrols an area.
    MovingRobotBehavior
    Implements the behavior context for a MovingRobot.
    MovingState
    Implements the "Moving" state for an enemy's state machine.
    PausedHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the pause menu.
    PausedView
    Renders the pause menu screen.
    PcTile
    Represents an interactable computer terminal (PC) tile in the game.
    PhysicsHandler
    A utility class containing static methods for handling game physics.
    PlatformTile
    Represents a solid platform tile that entities can stand on.
    Player
    Represents the player character controlled by the user.
    PlayerState
    Enumerates the possible states for the player character.
    PlayerView
    Renders the player entity on the screen.
    PlayingView
    Renders the main gameplay screen.
    PopupHandler
    Manages the state and logic for in-game popups, such as search progress bars and notifications.
    PopupView
    Renders in-game popups, such as notifications and search progress bars.
    ProfileManager
    A utility class for managing user profiles, including saving, loading, and deleting.
    ProfileSelectionHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the profile selection screen.
    ProfileSelectionView
    Renders the user profile selection screen.
    StandingRobot
    Represents a stationary enemy robot that does not patrol.
    StandingRobotBehavior
    Implements the behavior context for a StandingRobot.
    StatsHandler
    Handles user input for the statistics screen.
    StatsView
    Renders the statistics screen for the currently active user profile.
    TerminalHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the in-game terminal screen.
    TerminalView
    Renders the in-game terminal screen.
    Tile
    An abstract base class for all tiles that make up the game world's structure.
    TileFactory
    A factory class for creating different types of tiles.
    TileTypes
    Enumerates the different types of tiles that can exist in a game level.
    TurningState
    Implements the "Turning" state for an enemy's state machine.
    UIStyle
    A final utility class that centralizes UI styling constants.
    Usable
    Defines a contract for objects that can be "used" by an entity.
    UserProfile
    Represents a user's profile, storing all their progress and statistics.
    VictoryHandler
    Handles user input and logic for the Victory screen.
    VictoryView
    Renders the "You Win!"
    WallTile
    Represents a solid, impassable wall tile in the game world.
